        "content": "<p>I've noticed that <code>Std.MaxOrEq Int</code> is not synthetized by Lean, while <code>Std.MinOrEq Int</code> is. </p>\n<p>I wonder if this is an issue with the class instance not being synthetized correctly.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://live.lean-lang.org/#codez=MQZwngdgLgFgBAZSgEwHQFkCWECiBHAeQCc4BJaAKAtElkRQwEMAPfYsyoA\">MWE</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">synth</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MinEqOr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ✅</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">synth</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">MaxEqOr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- ❌</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 570198709,
        "sender_full_name": "Ayhon",
        "timestamp": 1769465810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Adding</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderSup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">max_le_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">max_le_iff</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LinearOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Std</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LawfulOrderInf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">le_min_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_min_iff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>to mathlib seems to fix it (<a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/34471\">#34471</a>)</p>",
        "id": 570205718,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1769469318
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Obviously this should also work without Mathlib imported, but we want the mathlib instances so that it works for an arbitrary linear order too.</p>",
